  "text": "Four Python source files in pandas-dev/pandas contain runtime dependencies on scipy.stats through direct imports. In pandas/core/nanops.py, the correlation_tools function (line 1622-1629) conditionally imports kendalltau and spearmanr from scipy.stats to compute Kendall and Spearman correlations respectively. In the plotting module, pandas/plotting/_matplotlib/hist.py (line 276) and pandas/plotting/_matplotlib/misc.py (line 84) both import gaussian_kde from scipy.stats for kernel density estimation in histogram visualizations. Finally, in the test suite, pandas/tests/groupby/test_reductions.py (line 1040) imports sem from scipy.stats in the scipy_sem helper function for testing standard error of the mean calculations. These imports are all conditional, occurring at runtime within functions rather than at module level, allowing pandas to degrade gracefully when scipy is not installed."
}

